### Session Expiry

The sessionStorage snapshot includes a `timestamp`. On restore, if more than 5 minutes have elapsed, we discard it and enter the Universe in normal strategic mode. This handles the case where the user navigated away, browsed other pages, and eventually landed back on `/universe`.

### Multiple Rapid Dockings

The docking callback is called exactly once (when state transitions to `'done'`), then reset. The `dockingStateRef` prevents re-entry because the state is `'done'` not `'none'`.

### Mobile: No Keyboard Required

Docking auto-triggers on proximity (viewZ < DOCKING_THRESHOLD_Z AND centered). On mobile, the player approaches stars using existing touch controls (which would need to be added separately -- but the docking itself requires no keyboard). The existing ENTER-to-read fallback remains for desktop users who are near a star but not close enough to auto-dock.

