```

We also need a `selectedGalaxyUserIdRef` (a ref that captures the userId whose galaxy we entered, set in `handleExploreGalaxy`), so we can reload the galaxy posts on return.

### Restore (in `Universe.jsx` on mount)

```js
useEffect(() => {
    const raw = sessionStorage.getItem('rocketSession');
    if (!raw) return;

    try {
        const session = JSON.parse(raw);
        // Only restore if fresh (< 5 minutes old)
        if (Date.now() - session.timestamp > 300000) {
            sessionStorage.removeItem('rocketSession');
            return;
        }

        // Set flag to show reverse warp overlay
        setReverseWarpActive(true);
        setRestoringRocketSession(session);

        // Clean up -- single use
        sessionStorage.removeItem('rocketSession');
    } catch {
        sessionStorage.removeItem('rocketSession');
    }
}, []);
```

The actual restoration happens once `postArray` is loaded (we need the galaxy posts):

```js
useEffect(() => {
    if (!restoringRocketSession || postArray.length === 0) return;

    const session = restoringRocketSession;
    const galaxyPosts = postArray.filter(p => {
        const uid = p.users?.id ?? p.user_id;
        return uid === session.galaxyUserId;
    });

    if (galaxyPosts.length === 0) return;

    setRestoringRocketSession(null);
    setUniverseMode('pilot');

    rocketMode.restoreFromSnapshot(session, galaxyPosts, stageSize);

